<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain><z:e sem="disease" ids="C0038505" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Congenital Abnormality" abbrv="PKWS">Sturge-Weber syndrome</z:e> without facial <z:hpo ids='HP_0003764'>nevus</z:hpo> is rare </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain>Twenty-four cases were previously reported </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="2" pm="."><plain>Although <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0022283" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Congenital Abnormality" abbrv="">hypomelanosis of Ito</z:e> is a relatively common disorder, there was only one previous case in association with <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0038505" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Congenital Abnormality" abbrv="PKWS">Sturge-Weber syndrome</z:e> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="3" pm="."><plain>We describe an 11-year-old boy with <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0038505" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Congenital Abnormality" abbrv="PKWS">Sturge-Weber syndrome</z:e> without facial <z:hpo ids='HP_0003764'>nevus</z:hpo>, coexistent with <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0022283" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome;Congenital Abnormality" abbrv="">hypomelanosis of Ito</z:e> </plain></SENT>
</text></document>